               <floruit notBefore="1530" notAfter="1578"> He was a sixteenth century 
                  Ethiopian monk who composed his personal as well as political life from
                  <date>1531</date> to <date>1578</date>. 
                  He received a monastic habit in <date>1531/32</date> 
                  in the monastery of <placeName ref="LOC2228DabraA">Dabra ʿAbbāy</placeName>. 
                  After  travelling around different places  including 
                  <placeName ref="LOC1310Aksum">ʾAksum</placeName> and 
                  <placeName ref="LOC2254DabraD">Dabra Dāmmo</placeName>, 
                  he settled in the monastery of <placeName ref="LOC1634Ayda">ʿAydā</placeName>.
                  His account provides important historical details about  the war of <persName ref="PRS1500Ahmad">ʾAḥmad</persName>, 
                  the capture of <persName ref="PRS7102Minas">Minās</persName>, 
                  the death of <persName ref="PRS4121Fiqtor">Fiqṭor</persName>, 
                  the incursion of <persName ref="ETH1973Oromo">Oromo</persName>, 
                  the death of <persName ref="PRS4406Gaewa">Gāʿǝwā</persName> 
                  and the campaign of <persName ref="PRS5043hamalmal">Ḥamalmāl</persName>
               </floruit>
                  
                  <death when="1578"/>
